FT  29 SEP 92 / Anti-British feeling causes job cuts
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LISA WOOD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A FORD union official yesterday claimed anti-British feeling had provoked
Ford of Europe to announce 1,500 job losses at UK car plants, Lisa Wood
writes.
Mr Andy Richards, convener at Bridgend, south Wales, one of the Ford plants
affected by the cuts, alleged that the management board of Ford of Europe
was 'dominated by Germans using their position in a nationalistic way.'
He said that job losses had only been announced for UK plants, not those in
France, Germany and Spain.
Ford said yesterday that only two members of the board were German, the rest
were mainly Americans.
