<HEADLINE>
FT  29 SEP 92 / Hospital trust fined Pounds 7,500
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE Anglian Harbours Hospital Trust, at Great Yarmouth, Norfolk, was
yesterday fined Pounds 7,500 for keeping filthy kitchens at two hospitals.
It is thought to be the first time a National Health Service trust has been
prosecuted since changes in hygiene regulations. The trust admitted before
Great Yarmouth magistrates to 22 charges under food hygiene regulations and
one under the Food Safety Act.
Mr Malcolm Savory, for the trust, said the fine would have to be paid from
money earmarked for patient services.
