FT  28 SEP 92 / Private companies 'optimistic'
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE RECESSION has bruised but not defeated private companies, according to a
survey of 1,000 owner-managers, published today by Pannell Kerr Forster, the
chartered accountants.
While 65 per cent claimed to work more than 50 hours a week and 44 per cent
described bank managers as having been 'distinctly unhelpful' in the
previous year, 64 per cent looked to improved performance for their
companies over the next. Job satisfaction was also relatively high: 57 per
cent said it had been 'fairly or highly satisfying' to run their businesses
in the past year.
