FT  28 SEP 92 / UK Company News: Ardagh tops IPounds 4m despite pressures
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Ardagh, the Dublin-based glass producer, made pre-tax profits of IPounds
4.21m, or Pounds 4.38m, in the 53 weeks ended June 30 1992.
That compared with IPounds 4.98m for the previous year, and the directors
considered it satisfactory in the light of the pressures on volumes and
margins.
Sales for the 53 weeks totalled IPounds 32.5m (IPounds 32.8m), while trading
profit came through at IPounds 3.43m (IPounds 4.11m).
Earnings per share were 11.18p (12.39p) and the final dividend is 2.39p for
a total of 3.115p (3p).
