FT  26 SEP 92 / World Stock Markets: Kuwait
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARK NICHOLSON, Middle East Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
KUWAIT's stock exchange reopens on Monday after a two-year closure forced by
the Iraqi invasion and the state's subsequent economic and financial
dislocation, writes Mark Nicholson, Middle East Correspondent. Shares in 31
companies, including five non-Kuwaiti groups, will be traded during a 2 1/2
 hour opening session. The market, which was capitalised at just over
Dollars 3bn before the Gulf war, is not expected for several months at least
to reach even the lowest pre-war daily turnover, which ranged between
Dollars 17m and Dollars 35m.
