FT  26 SEP 92 / Ford warns of over-capacity in the UK
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Ford, the leading UK vehicle maker, has warned union officials that it has
too much capacity in the UK.
The company has told white-collar unions that 62 salaried jobs must be cut
in the UK in addition to the 1,487 hourly paid jobs that are to be cut by
the end of the year.
Sales of its Fiesta and Escort/Orion cars and light vans were forecast 'to
remain low', said the company.
