<TEXT>
QUAKER Oats, the US foods group, has reached agreement to sell two Italian
businesses, Sorba and Pandea, to Garma, an Italian investment group, AP-DJ
reports.
Quaker said the two businesses, although profitable, do not fit its
strategic European core businesses of pet foods and cereals.
