In addition to realised losses of Pounds 700,000 on its development
portfolio, Mr Michael Wigley, the chairman, said that further provisions of
Pounds 3.2m had been made to reflect current values.
Lack of consumer spending resulted in a greater than budgeted operating loss
of Pounds 3.5m (Pounds 2.7m) at Stead &amp; Simpson.
Group operating losses were Pounds 3.9m (Pounds 1.1m profits). Losses per
share worked through at 31.3p (7.5p).
</TEXT>
