<HEADLINE>
FT  26 SEP 92 / UK Company News: First half profits warning at Leigh
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares in Leigh Interests, the waste management group, fell 51p to 175p
yesterday after a warning that profits for the first half to September 30
would be significantly below the corresponding Pounds 7.1m.
Mr Malcolm Wood, chairman, said that turnover had been held back by
depressed activity in the nationwide market for contaminated land
reclamation contracts and there had been delays in completing the
commissioning of the new facilities at Four Ashes, Wolverhampton.
However, he expected that during the second half Four Ashes would be
profitable and results for the period would be 'significantly in excess of
the first half'.
